▪︎ Keys in vim
<C> = Ctrl
<S> = Shift
<ESC> = ESC
<CR> = enter
<Down> = ↓ 

▪︎ normal mode - ESC
	gg 》Move the cursor to the beginning of the file.
	G 》Move the cursor to the end of the file.
	u 》to undo the last change.
	h 》move cursor ←
	l 》move cursor →
	k 》move cursor ↑
	j 》move cursor ↓
	p 》paste after the cursor.
	P 》paste before the cursor.
	C 》Delete from the cursor position to the end of the line and start insert mode.
	d0 》 Delete from the cursor position to the start of the line.
	D 》Delete the characters under the cursor until the end of the line.
	0 》cursor moves to the start of the current line.
	$ 》cursor moves to the end of the current line.
	b 》cursor moves to the start of the previous word.
	w 》Move the cursor to the start of the world.
	e 》Move the cursor to the end of the world.
	H 》move the cursor to the start of the displaying screen.
	M 》move the cursor to the middle line of the screen.
	L 》move the cursor to the end line of the screen.
	% 》Move the cursor to parenthesis or (curly/square) brackets ([{}]).

	ZZ 》 write and exit.
	ZQ 》 Qiut without checking for changeV 》 visual line mode.
	numberline G 》 go to number line.
	cit 》 go to in the tag.
	ci[({< 》 change in [({<. 
	dit 》 delete in the tag.
	0w 》 go to the beginning line.
	cw 》change word.
	ctrl+v 》 visual block mode.
	ctrl+b 》 move to scroll up ↑ the entire page.
	ctrl+f 》 move to scroll down ↓ the entire page.


▪︎ command mode - :
	:u 》to undo the last change.
	:n -fileName- 》 new file.
	:x 》 write and exit.
	:q! 》 Qiut without checking for changes.
	:vs :vsplit 》 split current window split Vertically.
	:e -fileName- 》 open file.
	:numberline 》 go to number line.
	:helpclose 》 help close.
	:q 》 quit from help
	:ls 》 show all buffers.
			%     the buffer in the current window.
			a     an active buffer.
			#     the alternate buffer.
			=     a readonly buffer.
			R     a terminal buffer with a running job.
            F     a terminal buffer with a finished job.
			u     an unlisted buffer
			
	

	:new 》 Create a new window and start editing an empty file in it.
	:sort 》 sort lines.
	:sort iu 》 sort lines and i casesenistive u uniqe.
	:sort! 》 sort lines from under.
	:terminal -shellName- 》 open terminal.
	:messages 》 print messages.
	:messages clear 》 clear messages.
	

▪︎ insert mode : i
	i 》 insert before cursor.
	a 》 insert after cursor.
	o 》 insert and new line.

▪︎ recording mode : q+namerecording.
	q 》 exit mode recording.
	
